        <briefdescription>
<para>An enum describing how a function is extrapolated outside the interpolation domain. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>PERIODIC</computeroutput> : the function is assumed to be periodic. The value at a point outside the domain is taken as the value at the equivalent point inside the domain.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>NULL_VALUE</computeroutput> : the function evaluates to zero outside the domain.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>CONSTANT</computeroutput> : the function is clamped to the value at the nearest boundary point. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
